---
// Privacy, plain-language note on what we collect and how we treat it. Marked
// as a starting draft for the volunteer group to confirm.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const mailto = `mailto:${SITE.email}?subject=${encodeURIComponent('Privacy question')}`;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How Our Ridge handles your details: what our newsletter and forms collect, where it lives, and your right to unsubscribe."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Your details, handled with care</h1>

      <div class="panel draft-note">
        <p style="margin:0">
          <strong>A starting draft.</strong> This is our plain-language privacy
          note, written to get us going. The volunteer group will review and
          confirm the wording, if anything here matters to you, please <a href={mailto}>ask us</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="lead">
        We're neighbours, not marketers. We only ask for what we need to keep you
        in the loop, and we never sell your information.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Newsletter &amp; join list:</strong> your name and email address.</li>
        <li><strong>Optional extras:</strong> your street or address, and the activities you're interested in, only if you choose to tell us.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact &amp; volunteer forms:</strong> your name, email, and whatever you write in your message.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where it lives</h2>
      <p>
        Your details sit in two places: our mailing list (the tool we use to send
        the newsletter) and our group email inbox. Only the volunteers helping run
        Our Ridge can see them.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>
        We use your information to send you Ridge news and event updates, to reply
        to you, and to organise the walks, rides and community activities you've
        shown interest in. That's it.
      </p>

      <h2>We never sell your data</h2>
      <p>
        We don't sell, rent, or trade your information, and we don't share it with
        the property developer or any business. We'll only ever share details if
        the law requires it.
      </p>

      <h2>Unsubscribing (your CASL rights)</h2>
      <p>
        Canada's anti-spam law (CASL) gives you the right to stop hearing from us
        whenever you like. Every newsletter includes an unsubscribe link, or you
        can simply <a href={mailto}>email us</a> and we'll take you off the list.
        You can also ask us what we hold about you, or ask us to delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>Reaching us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about any of this? Write to <a href={mailto}>{SITE.email}</a>.
        A real neighbour will get back to you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .draft-note { border-left: 4px solid var(--c-fern); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
</style>
